CNCP v1 23391
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13336: Type '\"enter\"' and '\"tab\"' is not assignable to type 'VOnModifiers'",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:20:53.271250+00:00",
  "text": "Type '\"enter\"' and '\"tab\"' is not assignable to type 'VOnModifiers'\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.14\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```javascript\n<script setup>\nimport { h, withModifiers } from 'vue'\n\nconst btn = h('button', {\n  onKeyup: withModifiers(\n    (e) => {console.log('keyup:', e.key)},\n    ['tab', 'enter', 'delete', 'esc', 'space', 'up', 'down', 'right', 'left']\n  )\n}, 'click')\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <btn />\n</template>\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nCorrect prompt\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n1. Type '\"enter\"' is not assignable to type 'VOnModifiers'\n2. Type '\"tab\"' is not assignable to type 'VOnModifiers'\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/14423910-cae1-4d89-b2b8-0f6d6fd0f0f8)\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nWindows 11 24H2\nMicrosoft Edge 136.0.3240.64\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
